  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Triptolide was shown in experimental studies to inhibit the cyst formation and growth in
      ADPKD models, while triptolide-containing formulation was revealed to potentially slow the
      disease progression in several proteinuric ADPKD patients in our clinical practice. It
      remains to be shown the effect of triptolide-containing formulation on total kidney volume
      (TKV) enlargement and renal function protection in ADPKD patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
